-- German Minister Sees ‘No Alternative’ to Euro, Handelsblatt Says
-- B y   N i c h o l a s   C o m f o r t
-- 2012-01-01T12:37:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-01/german-minister-sees-no-alternative-to-euro-handelsblatt-says.html
German Economy Minister Philipp Roesler sees “no alternative” to the  euro  for  Europe  to
compete with American and Asian markets, Handelsblatt reported,
citing an interview with the minister.  Roesler said recent agreements by European leaders to raise
stability in the euro area will strengthen the solidity of the
common currency, the Dusseldorf, Germany-based newspaper said in
an e-mailed summary of an article to be published in tomorrow’s
edition.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nicholas Comfort in Frankfurt at 
